+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xbv7BbCJfoyDupNzQ2mp2T","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Complete Codebase Overview\n\n### 1. Project Structure\nThe workspace is a notes API project with full-text search functionality being implemented. Files are organized as:\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts           (Database setup and seeding)\n│   ├── models.ts       (TypeScript interfaces)\n│   ├── routes.ts       (Express routes)\n│   ├── errors.ts       (Error handling)\n│   ├── server.ts       (Express app setup)\n│   └── seed.ts         (Database seeding script)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts   (15 CRUD tests)\n│   └── search.test.ts  (20 full-text search tests)\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── TASK.md\n```\n\n### 2. Database Setup (`src/db.ts`)\n- Uses **better-sqlite3** with WAL mode and foreign keys enabled\n- Creates `notes` table with: `id`, `title`, `body`, `tags` (JSON array as string), `created_at`, `updated_at`\n- Provides `createDatabase()` function (accepts optional path, defaults to `:memory:`)\n- Provides `seedDatabase()` function that inserts ~50 sample notes with tags\n- Sample notes cover diverse topics: programming, cooking, travel, science, music, health, etc.\n\n### 3. Models (`src/models.ts`)\n```typescript\ninterface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\ninterface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;\n  rank: number;\n}\n\ninterface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Routes (`src/routes.ts`)\nThe routes module exports a `createRoutes(db)` function that returns an Express Router with:\n\n**Implemented Routes:**\n- `GET /notes` - List all notes (optional `?tag=X` filtering using json_each)\n- `GET /notes/:id` - Get single note by ID\n- `POST /notes` - Create note (validates title and body required)\n- `PUT /notes/:id` - Update note (supports partial updates)\n- `DELETE /notes/:id` - Delete note\n\n**Not Implemented (needed for tests to pass):**\n- `GET /notes/search?q=<query>` - Full-text search with pagination and snippet highlighting\n- `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>` - Autocomplete suggestions\n\n### 5. Error Handling (`src/errors.ts`)\nTwo custom error classes with proper status codes:\n- `NotFoundError` (404) - for missing resources\n- `ValidationError` (400) - for invalid input\n\nPlus an `errorHandler` middleware that catches errors and returns appropriate JSON responses.\n\n### 6. Server Setup (`src/server.ts`)\n- `createApp(dbPath?)` - Creates Express app with routes and error handling\n- `createSeededApp(dbPath?)` - Creates app and seeds it with sample data\n- Can be run as main to start server on port 3000\n\n### 7. Seed Script (`src/seed.ts`)\n- Accepts optional database path argument (defaults to 'notes.db')\n- Creates database, seeds it with ~50 notes, and displays confirmation\n- Includes notes on diverse topics (50 notes total)\n\n### 8. Existing Tests - CRUD Tests (`tests/notes.test.ts`)\n**15 passing tests covering:**\n1. GET /notes returns all notes\n2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag\n13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n15. PUT updates updated_at times