hout being explicitly programmed. Key types include supervised learning (classification, regression), unsupervised learning (clustering), and reinforcement learning. Popular frameworks include TensorFlow, PyTorch, and scikit-learn.',\n   150→      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'ai', 'machine-learning']),\n   151→    },\n   152→    {\n   153→      title: 'Backpacking Through Southeast Asia',\n   154→      body: 'Southeast Asia offers incredible backpacking experiences on a budget. Visit ancient temples in Cambodia, pristine beaches in Thailand, rice terraces in Vietnam, and vibrant cities in Malaysia. Budget around $30-50 per day for accommodation, food, and transport.',\n   155→      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'asia', 'backpacking']),\n   156→    },\n   157→    {\n   158→      title: 'Sourdough Bread Baking Guide',\n   159→      body: 'Sourdough bread requires a mature starter, flour, water, and salt. The process involves mixing, autolyse, bulk fermentation with stretch and folds, shaping, cold retard overnight, and baking in a Dutch oven. The natural fermentation creates complex flavors and better digestibility.',\n   160→      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'baking', 'bread']),\n   161→    },\n   162→    {\n   163→      title: 'Introduction to Rust Programming',\n   164→      body: 'Rust is a systems programming language focused on safety, speed, and concurrency. Its ownership system prevents null pointer dereferences, dangling pointers, and data races at compile time. Rust is ideal for performance-critical applications, web assembly, and embedded systems.',\n   165→      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'rust', 'systems']),\n   166→    },\n   167→    {\n   168→      title: 'Climate Change and Renewable Energy',\n   169→      body: 'Renewable energy sources like solar, wind, hydroelectric, and geothermal are essential for combating climate change. Solar panel costs have dropped 89% since 2010. Wind energy is the fastest-growing power source globally. Transitioning to renewables can significantly reduce greenhouse gas emissions.',\n   170→      tags: JSON.stringify(['science', 'environment', 'energy']),\n   171→    },\n   172→    {\n   173→      title: 'Photography Composition Techniques',\n   174→      body: 'Great photography relies on strong composition. The rule of thirds places subjects at grid intersections. Leading lines guide the viewer eye. Framing uses natural elements to surround the subject. Symmetry creates balance. Negative space emphasizes the main subject by leaving empty areas.',\n   175→      tags: JSON.stringify(['photography', 'art', 'techniques']),\n   176→    },\n   177→    {\n   178→      title: 'GraphQL vs REST API Design',\n   179→      body: 'GraphQL lets clients request exactly the data they need in a single query, reducing over-fetching and under-fetching common with REST. REST uses multiple endpoints with fixed data structures. GraphQL has a single endpoint with a flexible query language. Both have tradeoffs in caching, complexity, and tooling.',\n   180→      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'api', 'web']),\n   181→    },\n   182→    {\n   183→      title: 'The Art of French Cooking',\n   184→      body: 'French cuisine is built on foundational techniques: the five mother sauces (bechamel, veloute, espagnole, hollandaise, tomato), proper knife skills, stock making, and mastering heat control. Classic dishes include coq au vin, beef bourguignon, ratatouille, and creme brulee.',\n   185→      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'french', 'techniques']),\n   186→    },\n   187→    {\n   188→      title: 'Hiking the Appalachian Trail',\n   189→      body: 'The Appalachian Trail stretches 2,190 miles from Georgia to Maine through 14 states. Thru-hiking takes 5-7 months. Section hiking is popular for those with less time. Essential gear includes a quality backpack, lightweight tent, sleeping bag, water filter, and proper hiking boots.',\n   190→      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', '